node.text:
Today is the last day of #mentalhealthawarenessweek. My name is Nicole, I am the founder of @selfcarecompany I truly believe each and everyone’s mental health journey is individual to them 💚 All of us are going at our own pace and there is no right or wrong. For years I ran away from my emotions because I was scared of them or embarrassed that others could see that I was struggling. So I hid it. Which only made my symptoms worse. After 10 years of severe anxiety effecting my day to day life. I realised that I was the only person who could heal me. Through allowing myself to feel everything rather than feel like I had to hide it. I am still working on this and I truly believe that looking after our mind is daily work. We must give ourselves so much love and kindness each day to overcome painful experiences we have had. You are never alone. We are all in this together. Another thing that changed my life is working with essential oils. When I was at my lowest I started making candles as a hobbie to help me relax, 4 years later I am lucky enough to collaborate with My Self Love Supply and send candles all over the world to help people with their anxiety, stress and low mood. We are so, so grateful for your support and blown away by how many of you are finding calm and peace whilst lighting your candles. Thank you so much for giving us a purpose. 
As you guys have loved the candles so much we have decided to extend the collaboration for the rest of the month of May. You can find our collab candle at selfcarecompany.com/candles (link also in bio). Use code BEKIND for 15% off 🌸
